{"/service/ndnp/scu/batch_scu_kiwi_ver03/data/sn84026912/00542866032/1923090501/0288.xml":{"full_text":"Jt. SOMETHING TO THINK\n.J. A no I T. 4*\nQuestionnaire is Sent to All South\nCarol inn Oonjjressiuen and\nSenators.\n(Charlotte. X. C.. Herald.)\nWe are publishing herewith daily\npress report of questions propounded\nto South Carolina members of Con\ngress by Commissioner of Agricul\nture I!. Harris, of Columbia, S. C.\nThis is the most important and far\nreaching questionnaire that has so\nfar emanated from any State official.\nMr. Harris strikes at the very roots\nof the economic cancer that is eating\ninto the vitals of agriculture and\nundermining civilization.\nIt requires more than ordinary\nmoral courage and honest conviction\nU prompt a man holding an import\nant State office to thus declare him\nself on the money monopoly as em\nbodied in the Federal reserve bank\ning system, and Commissioner Har\nris is to be commended for this ac\ntion. The common people, and es\npecially the farmers of South Caro\nlina, should rally to his support.\nFollowing is the clipping in full,\ntaken from the Daily Observer:\n\u2018\u2022Declaring that the financial sys\ntem of the United States must be\nsweepingly amended in order to\nguarantee to the agricultural inter\nests the protection to which they are\nentitled, Commissioner B. Harris, of\nthe State Department of Agriculture.\nCommerce and Industries, has an\nnounced that he was mailing a ques\ntionnaire to all Senators and Rep\nresentatives in Congress from South\nCarolina, asking them to reply to\nsix questions regarding the mone\ntary problems of the country.\n\u201cAs announced by Mr. Harris, the\nquestionnaire reads as follows:\n\u201c1. Who controls the money in\nthe United States?\n\u201c2. How much money per capita\nis in actual circulation at the present\ntime, and who says there should\nbe only so much money in circula\ntion?\n\u201c2. Who has the right to bring\na panic in the United States, and\nwhose business is it to keep a panic\nfrom happening?\n\u201c4. Is thero any reason for a\nmoney panic or a business depres\nsion in the United States?\nWho is it that protects the\nI'nited States from being invaded by\nforeign countries?\n\u201cfi. What is the greatest duty tiro\nUnited States owes its citizens?\n\u201cMr. Harris declared that, in his\nopinion, Congress is confronted by\nthe solemn duty of relieving the sit\nuation of the farming interests of\nthe country. The Federal reserve\neystem, he asserted, can he amended\nto provide for the necessary changes\nin the handling of this country's\nfinances.\u201d\nWe urge our readers to (study\nthese questions and evolve correct\nanswers to them. And for the benefit\nof those who may not have given any\nthought to the subject matter of this\nquestionnaire we submit, briefly, our\nanswers:\nQuestion 1. The Federal reserve\nboard controls the money in the Uni\nted States, but the allied bankers.\nWall street, control the Federal re\nserve board.\nQuestion 2. .fudge George W. rm\nstrong, of Dallas, Texas, himself a\nbanker, in his book. \u201cThe Crime of\n\u201920.\u201c shows conclusively by means\nof a most thorough lalysis. that the\nFnitcd States has only twenty dol\nlars ($20.00) per capita in actual\ncirculation, which is 40 per cent less\nIlian we had before the World War.\n\u201cAnd who says there should only bo\nso much money in circulation?\u201d\nWall street, through the Federal re\nserve board (a subservient agency),\ndetermines the volume of money in\ncirculation. The propaganda for a\nlimited volume of money is con\nducted (and paid for) by the money\nlending classes, whose selfish inter\nests (and big profits) make them de\nmand dear money and cheap labor\ncommodities. And these classes have\ndetermined all financial legislation\nfine? 1 SO 3.\nQuestion 3. Xo man or combina\ntion of men. no corporation or com\nbination of corporations, have either\na moral or legal right to bring a\npanic in the United States. Yet the\nFederal reserve hoard, with the aid\nand connivance of the war finance\ncorporation, at the dictation of .the\ne.llied hankers. Wall street, did pre\ncipitate the deflation panic of 1020,\nwhich continues to the present day.\nAnd \"whose lmisness is it to keep a\npanic from happening?\u201d This is the\nbusiness of Congress, for under the\nconstitution \"Congress alo.ie shall\nhave tho power to coin (create)\nmoney and regulate the value (quan\ntity) thereof.\" But Congress lias\nbeen and is false to the people, not\nonly in delegating all control over\nour money to private banking corpo\nrations. but in falling to take any\nefficient action to relieve tlie people\nfrom this artificial panic or prevent\nIts repetition. Three-fourths of the\nmembers of Congress should be re\ntired to private life on this issue\u2014\nthat they are false to the people on\nthe money question.\nQuestion 4. There is positively no\nreason in the world for a money pan\nic or a business depression in the\nUnited States\u2014absolutely none. Ev\nery money panic this nation has ev_r\nhad was due to a false and dishon\nest monetary standard and privately\ncontrolled and manipulated currency\nsystem. And every business depres\nsion is dire directly or indirectly to\ni he same cause. With a currency\nsystem administered by the govern\nment for the benefit of all the people\nand with a volume of currency\namply sufficient and always availa\nble to meet all legitimate demands\non short or long time loans--- and a\nrate of interest of only 2 per cent\nper annum, there would nevei again\nbe a business depression in the Uni\nted States. We challenge a refuta\ntion of the truth of this statement.\nWe are prepared to back it up with\nfacts and logical reasoning that can\nnot be denied\nSection 5. In the last analysis the\nprotection of our nation from for\neign invasion rests with the produc\ners of the nation\u2014those who work,\nthose who create, those who make\nhomes, those who live in families.\nIt is said that an army marchon\nits belly; it must be fed. it must he\nclothed, it must be equipped. All of\nthis is done by workers. And it is\nhere that we find true loyalty and a\npatriotism that is above price- that\ncannot be swayed by \"the profits of\nwar,\u201d The patriotism of the \"war\nprofiteers\u201d puts self-interest first,\nthe welfare of the nation second, and\nthe people he damned.\nQuestion 6. The greatest duty the\nUnited States owes its citizens is to\ndrive out the money changers from\nI the temple, the seats of government;\nto drive them out of the church: to\ndrive them out of our colleges and j\npublic schools; to drive out their in\ni fluence from the pulpit and the press\nand from our courts of justice (?).j\nAnd then establish government r>f\nand for and by the peoph1; the whole i\nj aim and purpose of all government\nbeing to promote the COMMON\u2019 j\nGOOD of ALL, THE PEOPLE; to j\ndethrone selfishness and privilege\nand establish justice, goodness and\nrighteousness in church and state.\nThe only way to do this is to set free\nthe money and credit of the nation\nand make money the servant of all\nI tlie people instead of their master,\nas it is under our present false mon\nj etary standard and special privilege\ntanking system. Abolish interest fo:\n1 private profit, for, as Thomas A. Edi\nson has truly said. \"Interest is an i\ninvention of Satan.\u201d And the Bible\ncondemns it.\nI This is not intended as an indict-\nment of the honorable men engaged\n1 in banking, or other honest money\nlenders; hut our W\u2019hole financial sys\ntem is wrong; it is a special privi\nlege; it is unjust to the workers of\nthe nation; it is the most destruct\nive institution in the history of gov\nernment. We have driven out alco\ni hoi\u2014the saloon\u2014hut where the sa\nj loon has destroyed its thousands,\nj our financial system, which includes\ninterest, has destroyed its tens of\nthousands.\nThe Alexander Reunion.\nThe Alexander reunion will be\nlield at the Alexander cemetery, near\nLittle River church, Oconee county,\non Saturday, Sept. 1.1th. All rela\ntives and friends are cordially in\nvited to attend this reunion. Tiie\nj address will be made by E.F.Watson,\na prominent attorney of Burnsville.\nI X. C., who is also a descendant of\nI D. D. Alexander, who was one of the\nfirst settlers of that community.\nASPIRIN\nSay \u201cBayer\u201d and Insist!\nUnless you see the name \"Bayer\"\nI on package or on tablets, you are not\ngetting the genuine Bayer product\nprescribed by physicians over twen-1\nty-two years and proved safe by mil\nliona for\nColds\nToothache\nEarache\nNeuralgia\nHeadache\nLumbago\nRheumatism\nVain, Pain\nAccept \u201cBayer Tablets of Aspirin\u201d\nonly. Each unbroken package con\ntains proner directions. Handy boxes\nof twelve tablets cost few cents.\nDruggists also sell bottles of 24 and\n100. Aspirin Is the trade mark of\nBayer .Manufacture of Monoacetlc\nacldester of \u00abal!cylicacid.\u2014adv.\nI Subscribe for The Courier. (Best.)\ni\nSTARTING\nOver200miles an\nhour-with balance\nWith the finer and finer balancing that designers have\nachieved in airplanes, their speed has been increased until\nthe record is now well over 200 miles an hour. A real tri\numph for the principle of balance.\nAnother similar triumph, less spectacular to be sure but just\nas important, is the production of a balanced motor fuel.\n\u201cStandard\u201d, the balanced gasoline, is refined and re-refined\n\u2014with the finest of modem equipment\u2014to give you every\nthing that you need in a motor fuel. Perfect starting\u2014a\nnimble pick-up\u2014the full power that only clean burning can\ngive you\u2014long mileage per gallon.\nBecause it is balanced, \u201cStandard\u201d meets every motor fuel\nrequirement consistently and economically.\nSTANDARD OIL COMPANY\n(New Jersey)\n^powerT'H\"\nAGE\nPropellers and mo-v\ntors alike need bal\nance to make the best\nwse of power. \u201cGas\u201d\nfor your car must be\nbalanced to make\npower itself ample,\nflexible* and cheap.\ncThe \u2018Balanced Gasoline\n4\nCOMMIMSM IN Itl'SSIA IS 1>I.A1>,\n\nSays American Who lias Had Oppor\ntunity to Study Conditions.\nWashington, Aug. 29.\u2014The storv\nof the saving of millions of lives of\nstarving and diseased in Russia by\nAmerican aid will be told \u201clovingly\nm Russian households for genera\ntions.\" Col. William X. Haskell de\nclared in a final report published to\nday on the activities of the Ameri\ncan relief administration in that\ncountry, of which he had charge.\nThe report, submitted to Herbert\nj Hoover, Secretary of Commerce and\nchairman of the relief administra\ntion, summarized the two years\u2019 re\nlief work which the gift of $60,000,\n0 00 by the American people and by\nCongress had made possible, and as\nsorted that it had won for America\nn lasting inheritance in good will of\nthe Slav races.\nDeclaring that communism in Rus\nsin is dead and the country is on the\nroad to recovery, Col. Haskell added\nthat the \u201crealization by the Russian\npeople that the strong American sys\ntem was aide and contained the\nspirit to save these millions of\nstrangers from the death that had\nengulfed thnn must have furnish\ned food for thought.\"\nThe checking of the famine and\nrestilence, he said, \u201chad turned the\ncorner for civilization in Russia,\u2019\u2019\nand lifted the Russian people from\ndespair to hope.\nBible the Most Translated Book.\nA dispatch from New York says:\nTlie Hililo is far in advance of any\nether hook in the number of trans\nlations. for it has actually been ren\ndered. in wl ole or in part, into 779\nlanguages and dialects, and the end\nis not yet in sight. The translation\nis still progressing at the rate of one\ncomplete book of the Bible in a new\nlanguage every six weeks a speed\nrecord which has been maintained\nfor over twenty years, according to\na writer in the Mentor for Septem\nber.\nWas Father of Twenty Children.\nAnderson. Aug. 29.\u2014M. W. Mer\niitt, a prominent fanner of the White\nPlains section of tiiis county, died\nlast night. He was the father of\nchildren, lo of whom are living.\nSubscribe for The Courier. (Best.)\nm:. O. W. GARDNER WHITES\nA Few Days\u2019 Meeting nt Coneross.\nThe Cliurdi at Walhalla.\n(Baptist Courier.)\nThe writer had the pleasure ot\nholding a meeting with the Coneross\nchurch, lasting from Sunday morn\ning, the 12th of August, including\nthe following Sunday, making eight\ndays of delightful worship and fel\nlowship, during which he preached\nmorning and evening. Both church\nand preacher were greatly \u2018freshed\nhv these services, and then vere not\nwanting evidences of interest upon\nthe part of the unsaved, though\nthere are not many in the commun\nity who are not church members.\nConeross church is three miles\nfrom Walhalla, located on a high,\ncommanding elevation upon the pub\nlic highway, surrounded by beauti\nful, well cultivated fields, with the\nmountains in full s'ght, and the peo\nple are prosperous, progressive farm\ners, with good homes, in which un\nstinted hospitality abounds. The\nchurch is among the stronger\nchurches of the Beaverdam Associa\ntion, and is capable of doing great\nthings under the right kind of lead\nership. At present it is without a\npastor, Brother L. H. Raines, the\nhead of the Long Creek Academy, to\nwhom the members were devoted,\nhaving resigned to give all his time\nto the school.\nThe Walhalla Church anil Pastor.\nWhile in Walhalla 1 learned of\nthe splendid spirit manifested by the\nFirst Baptist church towards its pas\ntor. Rev. L. W. Langston, whose\nhealth is far from being good. The\nchurch granted him leave of absence\nuntil May. 1 924, with his salary con\ntinued. This speaks louder than\nwords for both church and pastor.\nLangston is very much loved, and\nthe church proves by this act that\nit has the spirit of the Master. May\nthe blessings of the Lord be upon\nboth in a very large measure.\nCl. W. Gardner. j\nGreenwood. Aug. 21. 1922.\nPiles Cured in 6 to 14 Days\nDrugcists refund money if FA70 OINTMENT fails\nto cure 1 tchinit, Blind, fticcdir.it or Prntrudioft Piles\ntotantly rdievre behind and you^can ret\nThe Fnited elates Bureau of\nstandards is conducting an investi\ngation of electrolytes with a view\nto lengthening the service of stor\nage batteries.\nISSUANCE OF TAX EXECUTIONS\nNot to He Used for Collection of I*ri\nnte Debts\u2014Sheriffs Warned.\n(The State, Aug. 30.)\n\u201cThe tax machinery of South Car\nolina will not be used as a debt-col\nlecting agency.\u201d Such is the explana\ntion of Walter E. Duncan, Comp\ntroller General of this State, of in\nstructions sent all sheriffs, directing\nthem to seize only such of default\n'ng tax-payers\u2019 estates as may oe\nnecessary to raise moneys due the\nState anti county. \u201cSheriffs,\u201d Mr.\nDuncan said, \u201chave no authority to\nseize and sell any more of a tax-pay\ner\u2019s property than is required to\nmeet the amount owed as unpaid\ntaxes. A man should not be de\nprived of his home when he can\nsave it, and the State, certainly,\nshould not be a party to any effort\nto deprive any citizen of a home\nwhen this home may possibly be pre\nserved.\u201d\nThe sending out of instructions\nintended to put an end to the prac\ntice of collecting mortgages through\ntax executions was occasioned by the\nreceipt by Mr. Duncan of various\ncomplaints that the practice was be\ning resorted to in various sections\nof the State.\n\u201cMy attention has been called.\u201d\nthe Comptroller General said, \u201cto\nthe fact that mortgagees of land in\nvarious counties are disposed to set\ntle their mortgage claims by the sale\nof such lands under tax executions,\nprobably regarding this the cheap\nest way to foreclose their mortga\nges. This I consider to be against\nthe public interests, oftentimes\nworking undue hardship upon the\nmortgagor, who might, in many in\nstances, be able to retain his home\nby the sale, under execution, of suf\nficient personal property, or a por\nlion of his land, to pay his taxes.\nThis is particularly true in cases\nwhere homes are mortgaged for\nmore than these will sell for at pub- I\nlie outcry at this time and under Die\npresent existing conditions, noth\nthe mortgagor and the mortgagee\nare entitled equally to protection\nunder the law, designed as it is to\naccommodate and shield both from\naggression ind injustice: but the\ntax machinery of the State should\nnot and must not be used to benefit\none at the expense of the other.\n\u201cIn selling property for taxes un\njder execution the sheriffs of the va\nrivis counties of the State are ad\n\\ised and directed to adhere strictly\nto the law, which expressly provides\nthat \u2018the sheriff shall seize and take\nexclusive possession of so much of\nthe defaulting tax-payer's estate,\nreal or personal, or both, as may be\nnecessary to raise the sum of money\nnamed therein, and said charges\nthereon.' (From Section 522. Vol.\n2, Code of Laws, S. C., 1022.)\"\nThe Brucke-H ubbanl Reunion.\nThe Brucke-Hubbard reunion will\nbe held at the old home of Myra\nBrucke (near Bethel Presbyterian\nchurch) on Saturday, Sept. S. All\ntelatives and friends are invited to\ncome and bring well-filled baskets.\nLet's make this a more successful\nreunion than any ;n the past.\nMrs. Mena Alexander,\nMrs. Pelza Bell.\nSafety razors made in America\nare sold in England for less than\nthose of British manufacture.\nBE'NG thicker, the\namous Good\nyear All-Weather\nTread carries you\nlarther than other\ntreads. And it car\nries you in greater\nsafety, too. The big\ntough sharp-edged\nblocks cut deep and\ngrip tight on any\nsurf ace.They are tl o\nbest tire insurance\nagainst skidding\nyou can buy.\nAt Goodyear Service Station\nDealert we tell and re com\nmend the new Goodyear\nCord* with the. bcoeiea All\nWeather Tread and back\nthem up with ttandard\nGoodyear Service\nPIEDMONT MOTOR CO.,\n